### Test PO Creation Without Vendor
### This tests the enhanced automation service that creates POs even without vendors

### 1. Login to get JWT token
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@demo.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Create a requisition without preferred vendor
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/requisitions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

{
  "title": "Test Requisition Without Vendor",
  "description": "Testing PO creation without vendor requirement",
  "department": "IT",
  "priority": "medium",
  "totalAmount": 1500.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "budgetCode": "IT-2024-001",
  "costCenter": "CC-IT-001",
  "requiredByDate": "2024-02-15T00:00:00Z",
  "items": [
    {
      "description": "Laptop Computer",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 1200.00,
      "amount": 1200.00
    },
    {
      "description": "Mouse and Keyboard Set",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 300.00,
      "amount": 300.00
    }
  ]
}

### 3. Submit the requisition for approval
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/requisitions/{{requisition_id}}/submit
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 4. Get workflow status to see current stage
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/documents/{{requisition_id}}/approval-status
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 5. Approve the requisition through workflow (replace task_id with actual task ID)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/approvals/{{task_id}}/approve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

{
  "signature": "admin_signature",
  "comment": "Approved for testing PO creation without vendor"
}

### 6. Check if PO was auto-created
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/purchase-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}

### 7. Get the specific requisition to see auto-created PO metadata
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/requisitions/{{requisition_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt_token}}